        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 31–39. Pseudachorutes variabilis sp. nov. (31–35, 37–39) and P. subcrassus (36): 31, 33, head chaetotaxy (two different specimen); 32, 34, chaetotaxy of Abd. V–VI (two different specimen); 34a, shape of setae (Japanese specimen); 35–36, labium; 37, tip of tibiotarsus with unguis; 38, right and left mandibles; 39, Ant. III–IV (ventral side). Scales: Figs 31–34 = 0.1 mm, 35–39 = 0.01 mm." ;
